Class Camp

java.lang.Object
Camp
public class Camp extends Object
The Camp class represents an event or program organized by a school or a specific faculty. It includes information such as the camp name, start and end dates, registration details, user group who is allowed to attend the camp, location, available slots, committee slots, description, staff in charge, committee members, attendees, and visibility status.

The class provides methods to access and modify these attributes, ensuring proper encapsulation and control over the camp-related information.

      Parameters:
      campName - The name of the camp.
      startDate - The starting date of the camp.
      endDate - The ending date of the camp.
      registrationClosingDate - The closing date for camp registration.
      userGroup - The targeted user group (e.g., faculty or whole school).
      location - The location where the camp will take place.
      totalSlots - The total number of attendee slots available.
      campCommitteeSlots - The total number of committee slots (up to 10).
      description - A brief description of the camp.
      staffInCharge - The staff creating the camp.
      listOfCampCommittee - The list of students forming the camp committee.
      listOfAttendees - The list of students registered as attendees.
      visibilityToggle - The visibility status of the camp.
